Building Pidgin, Finch and libpurple
====================================

Pidgin, Finch and libpurple are built with the Meson build system and the
Ninja backend.  The old Autotools (./configure && make) build has been
removed; Meson is now the only supported way to build.


Requirements
------------

  * meson  (>= 0.56.0)
  * ninja
  * a C compiler (gcc or clang)
  * pkg-config
  * GLib 2.x development files
  * GTK+ 2.0 development files          (for the Pidgin GTK client)
  * ncurses / libgnt development files  (for the Finch console client)

Optional dependencies enable extra features (all auto-detected unless you
force them off): GnuTLS or NSS (TLS), Cyrus SASL, GNU libidn, Avahi
(Bonjour), GStreamer (sound/media), GtkSpell (spell check), D-Bus, Perl,
Tcl/Tk, SQLite3.


Quick start
-----------

    meson setup build
    ninja -C build
    sudo ninja -C build install

Then run 'pidgin' (GTK client) or 'finch' (console client).


Choosing a prefix
-----------------

    meson setup build --prefix=/usr/local
    ninja -C build
    sudo ninja -C build install


Build options
-------------

List every option and its current value with:

    meson configure build

Options are set at setup time (or reconfigured later) with -D<name>=<value>.
A few common ones (see meson_options.txt for the full list):

    -Dgtk=enabled|disabled|auto      Build the Pidgin GTK+2 client
    -Dgnt=enabled|disabled|auto      Build the Finch console client
    -Dssl=auto|gnutls|nss|none       TLS backend
    -Dgstreamer=enabled|disabled     Sound / voice&video media support
    -Ddbus=enabled|disabled          D-Bus remote-control support
    -Dperl=enabled|disabled          Perl plugin loader
    -Dtcl=enabled|disabled           Tcl plugin loader
    -Dplugins=true|false             Loadable plugin support
    -Dnls=true|false                 Native language support (gettext)
    -Dprotocols=irc,jabber,simple,bonjour,null   Which protocols to build

Example:

    meson setup build -Dssl=gnutls -Dgstreamer=disabled -Ddbus=enabled

To change options on an already-configured build directory:

    meson configure build -Dgstreamer=disabled
    ninja -C build


Running the test suite
----------------------

    meson test -C build


Cleaning
--------

Remove the build directory to start over:

    rm -rf build
